      "side": 1,
      "message": "[info] Line 65: The two upper-bound clamps re-derive the paired dimension but never re-check the minimum. On a display whose available size is smaller than minimumWidth/minimumHeight (e.g. a very small secondary screen, or an unusually tall/wide video where maxHeight/videoInvAspect \u003c minimumWidth), the final newWidth/newHeight can be pushed below the minimum. Consider re-applying Math.max(minimumWidth/Height, ...) after each max clamp, or asserting max \u003e\u003d min, so the result can never violate the minimum size. Minor/defensive, since normally the screen exceeds the min window.",
      "revId": "876e247c6b1556f8f5c9758820ef1d46cd71c531",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
